Wehner is also sceptical - and this scepticism is shared by many - that politeness leads to true cooperation.
"I see a lot of what happens from today until 2012, as a pre-match, or shadow boxing, for the main event of 2012," he said.
The reasons for this have much to do with the presentation of the new Republican majority in the White House and with the tea party voters who served their education.
No matter how worried the Republican leaders may be that they are poking too high, they know that they need to try to keep their promises to cut government spending and override health reform.
