In tap water, the analyses have revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
At dinner, the salmon steak with 34 identified chemical residues was the "most abundant" and even the plastic plate used to warm up the meal in the microwave was not unloaded.
The final risk of this "harmful cocktail" for the consumer is probably "undervalued", the study says.
In turn, the Alliance Europe Ecology-Les Verts (EE-LV) has proposed "in view of the urgency of the situation" to introduce a moratorium on the use of pesticides to stop the "increase in diseases of civilisation".
In July, a study by the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) on the presence of residues identified 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables that are consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
